JEREMIAH 29:11, “For I know the plans I have for you,” declares the Lord, plans to prosper you and not to harm you, plans to give you hope and a future."
Indeed, He is the author of each individual's life. He knows what's in store today, tomorrow and the future. He knows every single thing. Our life's story has already been written by Him who brought us in this world. He even knows when our very last breath is. He knows when your down and troubled. He even knows the number of every strands of hair that we have. He already knows the thing that we need before we ask Him. 
Most importantly, he knows that we are too weak and vulnerable; we are limited and incapable to save ourselves from the eternal fire. That's why He gave up His only son, Jesus Christ, FOR YOU AND ME.
As the AUTHOR and the FINISHER of our life's story, he has the greatest plan underlying ahead of us. Don't lose HOPE let your FAITH fan into flame.
Goodnight everyone and to the other side of the globe, Good morning!
#faithhopelovefuturehappinessjoy

answers.name: Demar Byas
answers.text:
#faith #believe #Pray #DontGiveUp #EvenWhenItGetsTough #courage #courage #believe #GodsPlan forYou #purpose 
To have faith is to be sure of the things we hope for, to be certain of the things we cannot see. (Hebrews 11:1 GNTD) 

Are You Hopeful? When you think about the future, are you hopeful? Or do you struggle with a sense of dread? People who have seen God's faithfulness in the past tend to be very hopeful about the future. They know a bad situation can turn into a wonderful testimony in a matter of minutes. On the other hand, people who have lost all hope view life from the perspective of dread. A close cousin to fear, dread steals the ability to enjoy ordinary life and makes people anxious about the future. 

Hope is the opposite of dread, and a close relative of faith. When we have faith in God, it leads to hope, and our outlook on life and the future is positive. Hope allows us to leave our unanswered questions in God's hands; it empowers us to remain at peace, and it enables us to believe the best about the days to come. You can have hope when you trust in God's love. He has the power to provide for you and lead you through every situation. 

Prayer: God, I choose to put my faith in You, knowing that it will turn into hope. I don't have to dread, because You have the ability to care for me, so I put my hope in You. In Jesus name Amen

YOU HAVE TO REPENT TO BE BORN AGAIN!

The apostle Paul once said that everywhere he went, he preached the same message to everyone: #Repentance# toward God and #faith# in the Lord Jesus Christ (Acts 20:21). 

These are the two requirements to lay a good foundation in your life and to be born again. 
God has joined *repentance* and *faith* together. But most Christian preachers have separated them. Repentance has been left out from most of today's gospel-preaching. Only faith is being preached by most preachers.

Note;

# YOU CANNOT HAVE FAITH IN JESUS WITHOUT REPENTING OF YOUR SINS AND HAVE SALVATION# 
(It doesn't work like that)

#YOU BEING GOOD/REPENTING OF EVIL ACTS WITHOUT FAITH IN JESUS, CANNOT GIVE YOU SALVATION EITHER#

READ---> ACT 20:21 
I have had one message for Jews and
Greeks alike--the necessity of repenting
from sin and turning to God, and of
having faith in our Lord Jesus. (NLT)

GOD BLESS YOU FOR READING.

To anyone:
- Just please listen. I have been in alot of peoples shoes. I honestly know how it is. Killing yourself isn't going to solve any problem. Pills will not clear any shame you have. Hurting your body by not eating will not make you look beautiful. Cutting yourself will not take the inner pain away. Smoking will not make your addiction any better. Drinking will not ease any sadness that you have. Killing yourself shows you gave up. Popping pills shows your weak and cant take it. Hurting your body just hurts you more than what you feel inside. Smoking just seems like a problem solver but in the end the problem is still there waiting to be solved. Drinking is a procrastinator it just prolongs the process of recovery. What you don't see is that YOU CAN DO THIS. You can be strong and live till the time God gave us is up. You can take any shame you feel inside and over come it. You are beautiful no matter what people say or think. You don't need a hit because you can solve anything and over come obstacle. You don't need a drink because you can do this. YOU CAN DO THIS. Anything is possible. So just know you if you are strong enough to over come any addiction then you are strong enough to over come anything life throws at you. I believe I you. Just have faith in God and have some patience. God gave you a life for a reason. Make him proud. #god #addiction #pills #drinking #cutting #likeforlike #likeforfollow #hurting #sorrow #shame #faith #patience #obstacles #YOUCANDOTHIS #believing #strength #perseverance #love #smoking #life

answers.name: Lily Collins ?????????
answers.text:
"Pray, hope and don't worry." - St. Pio of Pietrelcina ????

Went to St. Pio Chapel in Libis today. It was my first time to ask a saint to help me pray to God because they said that he was miraculous. When I was reading some of the testimonials of his devotees, I had goosebumps. Like, every single testimonial that I've read gave me goosebumps. I believe in miracles. But I've never heard such things came true because of the help of a saint before. It really moved me. While I was praying, I promised myself that whether my wishes will come true or not, if God will give me the chance to go to Italy, the first place I would go to is the Shrine of Padre Pio in San Giovanni Rotondo, Italy. And I would also ask my friends and family to go to St. Pio Chapel. ?

answers.name: The Everyday Reminder
answers.text:
Something to think about to be honest. A shame not much of us who are born into Islam realize that we are the ummah of an extraordinary man. And you were loved by him (pbuh) even before your parents loved you.
Think about it. Would your parents stay up for hours at night and pray till there was a puddle on the floor and until their feet swelled up? Forget that example, think about anyone you think cares about you. Would they do that for you? Would they deny food and drink from paradise and starve from hunger for days pleading with Allah to feed and clothe you first? Would they pray all night long and at hajj and every morning, afternoon and evening and in every salah for you? Would they?
You are an ummah that Allah has favored and you have what you have because of Muhammad's suffering. Why do we forget him?
Whenever you feel neglected just think about what real and intense love takes to prove, and then look at your prophet (pbuh). What compares to the love he had for you?

Do you neglect him even after all that?

And this company has surrounded me with amazing people who have #inspired me and grown me in my #faith. My prayer today is that our team continues to unashamedly combine our #betterhealth and our #betterfinances as way to strengthen our #walkwithGod. answers.name: Wendie Raelin Kelley
answers.text: #TBT to before I lost one of my greatest inspirations. My great grandma Kaiki was one of the funniest, most spirited, and sweetest women in my life. She introduced me yo my faith and helped me grow physically, emotionally, and spiritually. I have so many memories, but not enough space to write them all down. She taught me a lot about compassion and helping others. It's easy yo say I would no doubt be a completely different person if she hadn't been in my life. Each milestone I pass is difficult without her and my great grandpa, but I know that as long as I stick firm to my beliefs and do what I know to be right, they would both be proud of me. Today is one more day since I've seen her, but I know it's also one day closer. I love you Gram, and I can't wait to see you when it's the right time! #GreatGrandma #Memories #MarchTwentyFifth #Love #Faith
